   On the set of ``Hardball,'' after expressing his gung-ho
enthusiasm for the subject of jury nullification, Matthews
explained that his show needed to keep up a brisk pace.
</P>
<P>
   ``This isn't a news program,'' he said. ``People aren't tuning
me in for news. They're tuning me in as an alternative to
`Friends.' ''
</P>
