<HEADLINE>
TREASURY SALES LIST IS CONFINED TO BILLS 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The word PLUS in parentheses has been used instead of the
symbol, which is non-transmittable to many newspaper systems.) 
(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Tuesday's auction of three- and six-month bills.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.35 percent
and a six-month bill was 4.35 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Borg-Warner Automotive, $400 million of a 10-year bond,
Baa2/BBB(PLUS)/---. Merrill Lynch.
</P>
<P>
   Commercial Metals Co., $100 million in notes due in 2009,
Baa1/BBB(PLUS)/---. Goldman Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   Presidential Life Insurance, $100 million in unsecured senior
notes due in 2009. Ba1/BBB/---. BT Alex Brown.
</P>
<P>
   Temple-Inland, $300 million in intermediate maturity bonds.
A3/BBB(PLUS)/---. Warburg Dillon Read &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Georgia Capital Trust IV, 8 million shares of $25 trust
preferred securities due in 2009. A2/A-/---. Morgan Stanley Dean
Witter.
</P>
<P>
   Source: MCM Corporatewatch
</P>
<P>
   Ratings: Moody's Investors Service/Standard &AMP; Poor's Corp./Duff
&AMP; Phelps Credit.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY
</P>
<P>
   Boulder Valley School District Region 2, $63.6 million of
general obligation bonds. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Chicago Park District, $67.2 million of general obligation
bonds, 1999 series A, B and C. Siebert, Brandford, Shank &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas Independent School District, $165 million of unlimited
tax refunding general obligation bonds. Dain Rauscher Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Florida Housing Finance Corp., $190 million of homeowner
mortgage revenue bonds. Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana Health Facilities Finance Authority, $150 million of
hospital revenue bonds for Sister of St. Francis Hospital. Merrill
Lynch &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   New Hanover County, N.C., $120 million of regional medical
center bonds. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   New York State Dormitory Authority, $55 million of debt
securities for Brooklyn Medical Center. Bear, Stearns &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   New York State Research and Development, $155 million of debt
securities for LILCO. Lehman Bros.
</P>
<P>
   Ohio Housing Finance Authority, $200 million of single-family
mortgage revenue bonds. Lehman Bros.
</P>
<P>
   Palomar, Calif., $61.9 million of debt securities for Palomar
Health System. Paine Webber.
</P>
<P>
   Pennsylvania Higher Education Authority, $250 million of debt
securities for University of Pennsylvania Medical Center. PNC
Capital Markets.
</P>
<P>
   Public Building Commission of Chicago, $119 million of building
revenue refunding bonds. Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
