A5017 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     02-14 0745
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c. 1999 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; WHEN IT SEEMS HE CAN'T BE HIT ANYMORE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Whether you were for the President or against him, you've got to
agree with artist  &UR; Tom Trujillo  &LR; that ``No one has taken more of a
bashing than  &UR; Bill Clinton &LR; .''
</P>
<P>
   Apparently believing this to be good reason to hit him again,
Trujillo has created the ``Clinton Memorial Pinata,'' a paper
sculpture ready to be filled and almost 4 feet high.
</P>
<P>
   A limited supply of these is available, signed and numbered, for
$80 each. Trujillo's at tomkim &LR; got.net or (831) 685-1420. cq/pal &LR;
</P>
<P>
   P.S. According to  &UR; H.L. Mencken &LR; , ``Adultery is the application
of democracy to love.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; RICHARDS REFLECTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Renee Richards &LR; , the ophthalmologist and tennis star who was
 &UR; Richard Raskin  &LR; before 1975, told Tennis magazine that she has
certain regrets about making the change, especially having made it
at the age of 40.
</P>
<P>
   ``I get a lot of letters from people in their 40s who are
considering having this kind of operation,'' he said. ``And I
discourage all of them. ... If you're 18 or 20 and have never had
the kind of (advantages) I had, and you're oriented in that
direction, sure, go ahead and make right what nature didn't.
</P>
<P>
   ``But if you're a 45-year-old man and you're an airline pilot
and you have an ex-wife and three adolescent kids, you better get
on Thorazine or Zoloft or Prozac or get locked up or do whatever it
takes to keep you from being allowed to do something like this. ...
This is a much harder way to go than if I could have somehow kept
that compulsion and that side of me submerged. I couldn't do it.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - In front of a downtown theater in San Francisco last week, a
car with a sign identifying itself as one in a ``Reliable'' _ or
``reliable'' (eye witnesses are fuzzy) _ car service fleet had a
head-on collision with a street sign, which got knocked down.
``Reliable'' sat there, immobile, its nose pressed against ``No
Stopping.''
</P>
<P>
   - Did anyone notice that during one of the outdoor walk-arounds
on  &UR; Al Roker &LR; 's ``Today'' show last week, when he began conversing
with a man carrying a ``Hawaii'' sign, the man flipped it over to
reveal, ``NBC Supports Rape! Free  &UR; Lisa &LR; 
 &UR; Myers &LR; .'' The cameras broke away immediately. The New York Post
reported that the sign was a protest over the network's not airing
a Myers interview with a woman who had long ago accused
 &UR; Bill Clinton  &LR; of rape.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Samuel Beckett &LR; 's 35-second-long play ``Breath'' was
performed in London's West End last week. ``I just want to put on
record that I thought the whole evening was completely bogus and
pretentious,'' said one theater-goer.
</P>
<P>
   - If what you had in mind for that blank space over the sofa was
a drawing of  &UR; Charles Manson &LR; , you should have been at the
Antiquarian Book Fair in San Francisco over the weekend. Dealer
 &UR; Joe Luttrell &LR;  of Meyer Boswell Books was selling a series of
unsigned courtroom sketches made at Manson's 1971 trial.  &LR; Prices
rangefrom $150 to $450 each, ``depending on the power of the
drawing.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GO BEARS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - June Osterberg &LR; , guiding light of the Repair the Bear
Committee, received a $3,000 check last week in response to an item
here about the Marini Plaza bear repairs. The check, which covered
the rest of the money needed, was from  &UR; Elena Orsini &LR; 
 &UR; Court &LR; . Her maiden name means ``little bear''; she collects small
bears; her grandparents lived in North Beach; and her father,
 &UR; Caesar Orsini &LR; , lived and worked there all his life.
</P>
<P>
   - With stomach churning, &UR; John Worthington &LR;  forwards a letter
from the travel program of the California Alumni Association (of UC
Berkeley), describing a nature cruise in which the lecturer will be
`` &UR; Gunther Barth &LR; , professor enteritis of American history.''
</P>
<P>
   - The UC Berkeley Extension's Continuing Education in
Engineering Department sent students a memo about a class schedule
change: ``Starting on Monday, February 31 and ending March 13.''
Awestruck  &UR; Mark Burstein  &LR; is trying to imagine ``what'll happen on
Y2K k &LR; .''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Do you think music has the power to change lives?'' A: ``At &LR; 
 &UR; the end of the day, this is just pop music. It isn't like saving &LR; 
 &UR; lives. I don't think it matters too much. My job is to honestly &LR; 
 &UR; portray where I'm currently at and work as hard as I can. The &LR; 
 &UR; rest is up to fad, fashion and timing.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - Singer  &UR; Jewel &LR;  in Teen People.
</P>
</TEXT>
