<HEADLINE>
EDITORS: 
</HEADLINE>
  
 Sunday, Feb. 14, 1999      The Hearst News Service will file this story for Monday:   
(``HNS'' appears in all slug lines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLINTON-MEXICO (Merica, Mexico) _ President Clinton and Hillary
Clinton publicly put their affectionate relationship on display
Sunday by seeking out reporters aboard Air Force One to offer St.
Valentine's Day wishes and show off a gold-colored, heart-shaped
pin that the president gave his wife. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
</TEXT>
