<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HORRY HOSPITALIZED WITH CHEST PAINS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ Lakers forward Rick Fox's locker is adjacent to
Robert Horry's dressing cubicle, and Fox said the moment Horry
arrived at the Forum on Sunday he knew something was wrong.
</P>
<P>
   Call it intuition or a good memory, but a little while later
Horry was complaining of chest pains and taken to Centinela
Hospital Medical Center. Medical tests disclosed Horry had an
irregular heartbeat.
</P>
<P>
   Horry was scheduled to remain in the hospital overnight and is
expected to undergo additional tests this morning.
</P>
<P>
   It caused Fox think back to his days with the Boston Celtics,
and to Reggie Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis died of a heart problem while working out in a gym.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't know if it was heartburn, or what is was (with
Horry),'' Fox said. ``I know he just came off a virus and he was
sick. He had a cold and an upper respiratory infection. Sometimes
that can do it, but I'm not a doctor.''
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-10 Horry was in coach Del Harris' starting lineup
before his complaints sent him to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a shock to find out we didn't have Robert,'' Harris
said. ``I didn't know we weren't going to have him until our
players went out on the court. We're hoping the best for him.
That's the important thing right now.''
</P>
<P>
   Horry, who missed the season opener because of the birth of his
son, is averaging 5.5 points and 5.8 rebounds per game. Travis
Knight started in his spot, scored four points and had nine
rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Free throws: Fox spent the first 10 minutes after the game with
his feet in a bucket of ice water as he continues to nurse the foot
injury that kept him out of the first three games.... Crowd
favorite Eddie Jones scored 12 points in his 300th NBA game.
</P>
</TEXT>
